In a general triangle $ ADE$ (as shown) lines $ \overline{EB}$ and $ \overline{EC}$ are drawn. Which of the following angle relations is true?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt));
unitsize(2cm);

pair A = origin;
pair B = (1,0);
pair C = (2,0);
pair D = (3,0);
pair E = (1.25,1.75);

draw(A--D--E--cycle);
draw(E--B);
draw(E--C);

label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,S);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$D$",D,SE);
label("$E$",E,N);
label("$y$",E,3SW + 3S);
label("$w$",E,7S + E);
label("$b$",E,3SE + 4S + E);
label("$x$",A,NE);
label("$z$",B,NW);
label("$m$",B,NE);
label("$n$",C,NW);
label("$c$",C,NE);
label("$a$",D,NW+W);
\end{asy}
\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ x + z = a + b\qquad \textbf{(B)}\ y + z = a + b\qquad \textbf{(C)}\ m + x = w + n\qquad \\
\textbf{(D)}\ x + z + n = w + c + m\qquad \textbf{(E)}\ x + y + n = a + b + m$
